  %section(data-state="" )
    .title-information
    %h2 Wordpress blog (1/3)
    :markdown
      * create an OpenShift php-5.3 application
      * add a mysql cartridge.
        * $ rhc app create -t php-5.3 wordpress
        * $ rhc cartridge add -a blog -c mysql -p password
          * Note: save the MYSQL admin login and password!
      * cd to the app's php dir, get a copy of the wordpress software.
        * `$ cp WordPress_Download_Dir/wordpress-3.5.1.zip .`
      * unzip the wordpress code into this directory
        * $ unzip wordpress-3.5.1.zip
        * $ cd wordpress
        * $ cp wp-config-sample.php wp-config.php

  %section(data-state="" )
    .title-information
    %h2 Wordpress blog (2/3)
    :markdown
      * Edit wp-config.php and make the following changes:
        * `define('DB_NAME', $_ENV['OPENSHIFT_APP_NAME']);`
        * `define('DB_USER', $_ENV['OPENSHIFT_MYSQL_DB_USERNAME']);`
        * `define('DB_PASSWORD', $_ENV['OPENSHIFT_MYSQL_DB_PASSWORD']);`
        * `define('DB_HOST', $_ENV['OPENSHIFT_MYSQL_DB_HOST'] . ':' . $_ENV['OPENSHIFT_MYSQL_DB_PORT']);`

